726780f-a.title: Queens: Grand Avenue - 79th Street
726780f-a.text:
Grand Avenue, south side, between 79th Street and the New York Conecting Railroad. Eucene L. Armbruster states this house was erected in 189O by Christian Homever who sold it to the Brooklyn Dnion Gas Co. in 1915. However it has been the
home of C. Ulrick in May 1890.

726781f-a.title: Queens: Grand Avenue - 79th Street
726781f-a.text:
Grand Avenue, north side, west from 79th Street. The house seen in the foreground was a part of Washington ark. It does not appear inn the 1929 Queens Atlas. The New York connecting railroad extends through the site. The building in the backgrond which was used as a dace hall is now occupied by herry
Elein and Co. Inc.
July 1923.
Euccene L. Armbruster Collection
